- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/ResultsView.fs` and/or a 3-D sub-view in the `results` surface (render the 2-D orthographic projection of `placeElements`/`beamSegments` on the slice-002 Canvas host)
- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/OpticalConstructor.Ui.fsproj` (register any new `.fs` files)

## Testing plan

This is the LAST slice of the arc and carries the **full bundle gate set**
(run in order; first failure short-circuits): `build`, `unit-tests`,
`constructor-unit-tests`, `impl-log-structure`, `state-of-world-structure`,
`ui-smoke`, `ui-tests`.

- `ui-tests`: headless view tests assert Save writes `<name>.ocproj.json` and Open
  round-trips through the schema-validated path (AC-U8.1), template/gallery load
  via `Templates.loadTemplate` / `Help.openEntry` (AC-U8.2), theme/panel/dock
  changes persist via `UserEnvironment.save` and survive a restart (AC-U8.3), and
  the 3-D view renders a 2-D orthographic projection of `placeElements`/`beamSegments`
  on the Canvas host without GL (AC-U8.4).
- `ui-smoke`: every panel/page (including the 3-D view) renders one frame
  headlessly; the Canvas host renders without GL (┬¦U1.8 / ┬¦U8.4).
- `build`, `constructor-unit-tests`, `unit-tests`: green; no frozen edits.

## Risks

- **Medium: file-IO continuations + headless 3-D.** Open/Save use the Avalonia
  `IStorageProvider`, which MUST live in the host layer (┬¦0.5) and whose
  continuations MUST marshal back per ┬¦0.4. The 2-D-orthographic 3-D view MUST
  render on the Canvas host without a GL surface so the `ui-smoke` gate stays
  headless-green (┬¦U8.4). Environment persistence must round-trip
  (`UserEnvironment.save`) without introducing a new committable file type (┬¦0.6).

